"Not explicitly configured non-receiving mail domain (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls null-mx description"
msgstr ""
"Informational: Your domain that has A/AAAA records, clearly indicates that "
"it does not accept email by advertising a \"Null MX\" record. This is fine "
"if you do not want to receive email. Your configuration makes the subtests "
"in the STARTTLS and DANE category not applicable. This also goes for the "
"mail server specific subtests in the categories for IPv6 and DNSSEC."

msgid "test mailtls null-mx summary"
msgstr "Properly configured non-receiving mail domain (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls null-mx-with-other-mx description"
msgstr ""
"Warning: Your domain advertises a \"Null MX\" record indicating that it does"
" not accept email. However, on your domain a receiving mail server is set by"
" another MX record, making the \"Null MX\" conflicting. "

msgid "test mailtls null-mx-with-other-mx summary"
msgstr ""
"Inconsistently configured non-receiving mail domain (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls null-mx-without-a-aaaa description"
msgstr ""
"Warning: Your domain advertises a \"Null MX\" record indicating that it does"
" not accept email. However, your domain does not have A/AAAA records, making"
" the \"Null MX\" record unnecessary."

msgid "test mailtls null-mx-without-a-aaaa summary"
msgstr ""
"Properly configured non-receiving mail domain, though with unnecessary "
"record (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls passed description"
msgstr ""
"Well done! Sending mail servers supporting secure email transport ([STARTTLS and DANE](/faqs/starttls/)) can establish a secure \n"
"connection with your receiving mail server(s). STARTTLS prevents passive attackers from reading emails in transit to you. DANE protects against active attackers stripping STARTTLS encryption by manipulating the mail traffic."

msgid "test mailtls passed summary"
msgstr "Mail server connection sufficiently secured (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls title"
msgstr "Connexion sécurisée au serveur mail ?"

msgid "test mailtls unreachable description"
msgstr ""
"Test error: at least one of your receiving mail servers was not reachable "
"for us, making it impossible to (fully) test for STARTTLS and DANE. This "
"could be caused by network connectivity problems or by the mailserver(s) not"
" accepting connections."

msgid "test mailtls unreachable summary"
msgstr "Unreachable receiving mail server (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls untestable description"
msgstr ""
"Test error: at least one of your receiving mail servers was not testable for"
" us,  making it impossible to (fully) test for STARTTLS and DANE. This could"
" be caused by, among other things, SMTP errors and ratelimiting measures "
"engaging and dropping connections."

msgid "test mailtls untestable summary"
msgstr "Untestable mail server (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test mailtls warning description"
msgstr ""
"Too bad! Sending mail servers that support secure email transport ([STARTTLS and DANE](/faqs/starttls/)) can establish *no* or an\n"
" *insufficiently* secure connection with your receiving mail server(s). Passive and/or active attackers will therefore be able to read emails in transit to you. You should ask your mail provider to enable STARTTLS and DANE, and configure it securely."

msgid "test mailtls warning summary"
msgstr ""
"Mail server connection *not* or insufficiently secured (STARTTLS and DANE)"

msgid "test siteappsecpriv failed description"
msgstr ""
