" mechanisms to protect visitors against attacks involving, for example, "
"cross-site scripting (XSS) or framing. Through a security.txt file you can "
"provide researchers who have found a vulnerability on your systems, with "
"your contact infomation and your Coordinated Vulnerability Disclosure "
"policy. Note that HTTPS is a prerequisite for all tested security options. "
"Security headers (except for Referrer-Policy) are *not* relevant for domains"
" that redirect (through a 301/302 HTTP Status Code). "

