msgid "test siterpki failed description"
msgstr ""
"Too bad! At least one of the IP addresses of your web server and associated "
"name servers has a route announcement that is *not*  matched by the "
"published route authorisation ([RPKI](/faqs/rpki/)). This indicates an "
"unintentional or malicious route configuration error, that can be caused by "
"your web hoster or your name server hoster (internal error) or by a third "
"party (external error). In either case, it can lead to the unreachability of"
" your server or the interception of Internet traffic to your server. Contact"
" your web hoster or name server hoster as soon as possible. In the case of "
"an internal error, they should ask their network provider that owns your "
"server's IP addresses to fix the route configuration error."

msgid "test siterpki failed summary"
msgstr "*Unauthorised* route announcement (RPKI)"

msgid "test siterpki info description"
msgstr ""
"Informational: Your domain does *not* contain any name servers and thus "
"contains no web server IP addresses. There are no routable IP addresses that"
" could be tested ([RPKI](/faqs/rpki/))."

msgid "test siterpki info summary"
msgstr "*No* routable IP addresses found (RPKI)"

msgid "test siterpki label"
msgstr "Route authorisation (RPKI)"

msgid "test siterpki passed description"
msgstr ""
"Well done! All IP addresses of your web server and associated name servers "
"have a route announcement that is matched by the published route "
"authorisation ([RPKI](/faqs/rpki/)). As a result, visitors with enabled "
"route validation are better protected against various unintentional or "
"malicious route configuration errors, that can lead to the unreachability of"
" your servers or the interception of Internet traffic to your servers."

msgid "test siterpki passed summary"
msgstr "Authorised route announcement (RPKI)"

msgid "test siterpki title"
msgstr "Autorisation de routage ?"

msgid "test siterpki warning description"
msgstr ""
"Warning! At least one of the IP addresses of your web server and associated "
"name servers has a route announcement for which *no* route authorisation is "
"published ([RPKI](/faqs/rpki/)). As a result, visitors with enabled route "
"validation are *not* (fully) protected against various unintentional or "
"malicious route configuration errors, that can lead to the unreachability of"
" your servers or the interception of Internet traffic to your servers. "
"Contact your mail hoster or name server hoster about this. They can ask "
"their network provider that owns your server's IP addresses to publish "
"routing authorizations."

msgid "test siterpki warning summary"
msgstr "Route authorisation *not* published (RPKI)"

